description:
Bandit Sonic is one of the most famous cowboys around these here parts. Some would even say he runs the town... but what about when and even more famous/sexy/rich cowboy with flowing blonde hair comes to town? Can Sonic keep is status or will it go down the toielt with the rest of his pride?
Consider supporting my art on patreon if you're a fan and don't forget to like and subscribe ;)
https://www.patreon.com/Tamers12345

replies.text:
@Hou  

"The falseness of an opinion is not for us any objection to it: it is here, perhaps, that our new language sounds most strangely. 

The question is: how far an opinion is life-furthering, life-preserving, species-preserving, perhaps species-rearing, and we are fundamentally inclined to maintain that the falsest opinions (to which the synthetic judgments a priori belong), are the most indispensable to us, that without a recognition of logical fictions, without a comparison of reality with the purely IMAGINED world of the absolute and immutable, without a constant counterfeiting of the world by means of numbers, man could not live—that the renunciation of false opinions would be a renunciation of life, a negation of life. 

TO RECOGNISE UNTRUTH AS A CONDITION OF LIFE; that is certainly to impugn the traditional ideas of value in a dangerous manner, and a philosophy which ventures to do so, has thereby alone placed itself beyond good and evil."

comments.text:
This couldn't have come out at a better time, I got into an argument with my grandfather today over which Sonic cartoon was better: Sonic X or SU. I of course put forth evidence as to why SU is clearly superior. My grandfather simply ignored all reasoning and than had the balls to tell me that your videos don't even follow the canon of SU. Well, let's just say I beat the shit out of him after that. He hasn't gotten up off the floor since than, he's probably too much of a bitch to move cuz he knows I'll beat his ass again if I see him.

Anyway, I'm just glad I can watch this new episode and relax after such a stressful day. Thank you Tamers.
